  "text": "Tissues were prepared by intracardial perfusion with PBS followed by 1% PFA/PBS, 30% Sucrose/ PBS, OCT (Tissue-Tek) and cryosectioned at 50 mm. Blocking and staining was performed in PBS/3% BSA/0.2% Triton X-100 solution. Controls and experimental samples were always placed on the same slide, stained in parallel and imaged with the same parameters using confocal Zeiss LSM510 Confocal Microscope (Columbia Core Facilities). We used confocal microscopy to reconstruct whole cells from the image stacks and estimated the amount of protein per cell by measuring total fluorescent signal. Antibodies are listed in Supplementary file 5. Data were analyzed using Fiji (ImageJ). Digoxigenin-labeled antisense riboprobes were generated from cDNAs using reverse primers containing a 5' T7 polymerase promoter sequence (Supplementary file 5; [CITATION_1] . ",
